    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-06-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-06-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="64"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d64">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 033.3211/50.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-06-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 17, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose for the Division of
                    Information the following press clippings<note n="1" xml:id="d64fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> relating to the visit of Dr. Lauro Müller, Brazilian
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs, to the United States, and to the effect which that
                    visit is producing in Brazil [description of clippings.]</p>
                <p>It will be observed that both the editorials and the press telegrams refer to the
                    remarkable cordiality with which Dr. Lauro Müller has been received both by the
                    Government and the people of the United States and to the gratifying impression
                    which his reception has made both upon him and upon the Government and people of
                    Brazil.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin V. Morgan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
